<Br>
<font face=helvetica size=2 color=#000080><b>Bringing out the Trek in you</b> - 18:43:48</font>
<br><br><blockquote>
Looks as if interviews are the order of the news sites for the past couple of days. Amist it all though is a good interview by the guys over at <a href=http://www.theoxygentank.com/>The Oxygen Tank</a> with Kim Lathrop, who is currently working on Star Trek Voyager: Elite Force for <a href=http://www.ravensoft.com/>Raven Software</a>. Topics range from the normal interview questions and on to some end depth looks into working with the Q3 engine.
<br><br>
Here is one Q&A from the interview to get you started:
<br>
<blockquote>
<br>
<b>The Quake 3 engine has unprecedented possibilites when it comes to creating different types of realistic surroundings. In what ways is the engine making it possible for evironments in the game to look as close as possible to the actual show?</b>
<br><br>
As well as the patented Quake goodness that we've all come to be familiar with, Mr. Carmack has provided us with the wonderful addition of curve technology which allows us to create, well, curves! It's come in handy for recreating such elements of Voyager as the bridge--the bridge ceiling, the tactical panel that forms the back wall, the tactical and ops stations, the walls in Janeway's ready room, the front windows of the conference room, the turbolift, the warp core...if you think about it, how many of the architectural elements of the U.S.S. Voyager are not curves? We'd have a pretty blocky Voyager if not for that little addition. In addition to what you'll see on Voyager, our level designers have taken curve technology and gone off the deep end with some of the alien environments that we've created exclusively for the game! I can honestly say people will be surprised by the quantity of truly curved surfaces that have never been seen in games before.
<br>
</blockquote>
Go ahead and click <a href=http://www.theoxygentank.com/interviews.shtml?id=lathrop>here</a> to read the rest.  You know you want to.



<b><p align=right>Update by <a href="mailto:"></a></p></b>
</blockquote>
<h3>Go <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net">back</a> to the main news page...</h3>
